{"author":{"id":"8e1777f58c0cfe5478428be8f9fcbfe90d25e44689578335da8fc2246fe0915a"},"ops":[{"type":3,"timestamp":1736363217,"nonce":"h15NxQ/BKEDnupTFl+MAwGj6TaQ=","metadata":{"github-id":"IC_kwDOAW4Y0s6Zr5ug","github-url":"https://github.com/galaxyproject/tools-iuc/issues/6661#issuecomment-2578422688"},"message":"Galaxy is setting TMPDIR for you as part of the job_script, can you check your job_scripts (mine for example is called `galaxy_77617537.sh` in the JWD).\n\nYou should see something like that:\n```\nTMP=\"${TMP:-$TEMP}\"\nTMPDIR=\"${TMPDIR:-$TEMP}\"\n\nTMP=\"${TMP:-$TMPDIR}\"\nTEMP=\"${TEMP:-$TMPDIR}\"\n\nTMP=\"${TMP:-$_GALAXY_JOB_TMP_DIR}\"\nTEMP=\"${TEMP:-$_GALAXY_JOB_TMP_DIR}\"\nTMPDIR=\"${TMPDIR:-$_GALAXY_JOB_TMP_DIR}\"\n```\n\nYou can also see it here in the default job template: https://github.com/usegalaxy-eu/galaxy/blob/release_24.1_europe/lib/galaxy/jobs/runners/util/job_script/DEFAULT_JOB_FILE_TEMPLATE.sh#L52\n\n\u003e Can you please explain how and where do you set TMPDIR for Galaxy EU, so we can try to replicate it ?\n\nOn EU we set TMPDIR / TEMP etc via TPV. Are you running TPV as well? And we overwrite the default tempfile location if we need to. So the default location for tempfiles should be already GALAXY_JOB_TMP_DIR. I think also in your case if you are not overwriting it. And TMPDIR should be set during the job execution on your system already and should point to GALAXY_JOB_TMP_DIR.\n\n\u003e While we do understand your concern about not exposing internal galaxy logic, those reserved variables are documented publicly and some, such as GALAXY_SLOTS are present in the tool wrappers.\n\nYes, we try out best :) But there is no community standard to specify number of cores and to be fair we always set a default value. In the case the deployment don't offer the `GALAXY_SLOTS` variable (which should not happen in Galaxy) the tool would fallback to a default value specified by the wrapper. \n\n\u003e For some expert users, the flexibility to set custom temporary path is indeed nice, but for most of ours users having a transparent process where they don't have to deal with the (temporary) files, and instead trust Galaxy configuration ( set by admins) could be appropriate.\nWe suggested using the job working directory, because it' specific to Galaxy and customisable by configuration. In addition, it doesn't rely on an external dependency that could be undefined.\n\nThis is already how it should work. Can you provide me a job script on your setup? Please ping me on Matrix, I guess the issue you are seeing here is an Admin problem, not a tool problem.","files":null}]}